The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Chennai to get new stadium

Chennai: A state-of-the-art cricket stadium of international standard would be built near Chennai to host the 2011 World Cup, Tamil Nadu government announced on Monday. 

The decision was taken at a state cabinet meeting headed by chief minister M. Karunanidhi. 

The government would lease 50 acres of land in Karunguzhipallam village near the IT Corridor to the Tamil Nadu Cricket Association (TNCA) following its request, an official release here said. (PTI) 




